                },
                "page": 298
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Skeleton",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Skeleton Abilities",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sections": [
                        {
                            "name": "Unlife without Flesh",
                            "type": "sidebar",
                            "sections": [],
                            "text": "The necromantic energies that infuse animated undead skeletons give them the ability to see without eyes and move without muscles. Despite being mindless, skeletons\u2019 instinct to evil comes from their corrupt vital essence, perverting negative energy for creation rather than destruction.",
                            "source": {
                                "name": "Bestiary",
                                "link": {
                                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                                },
                                "page": 298
                            },
                            "subtype": "additional_lore",
                            "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": " Most skeletons have one of these abilities. If you give a skeleton more, you might want to increase its level and adjust its statistics.<br/><b>Bloody</b> The skeleton is covered in dripping blood and gains fast healing equal to its level. <b>Collapse</b><img alt=\"Reaction\" class=\"actiondark\" src=\"Images\\Actions\\Reaction.png\" style=\"height:15px; padding:0px 2px 0px 2px\"/><img alt=\"Reaction\" class=\"actionlight\" src=\"Images\\Actions\\Reaction_I.png\" style=\"height:15px; padding:0px 2px 0px 2px\"/><b>Trigger</b> The skeleton is critically hit. <b>Effect</b> The skeleton collapses into a pile of bones and the attack deals only normal damage. The skeleton can reform in a standing position as an action, but until it does, it is immobilized and fiat-footed.<br/><b>Explosive Death</b> When the skeleton is destroyed, its bones shatter and explode as the necromantic energy holding it together is released. Adjacent creatures take 1d6 slashing damage per 2 levels (minimum 1d6) with a basic Reflex save.<br/><b>Screaming Skull</b><img alt=\"Two Actions\" class=\"actiondark\" src=\"Images\\Actions\\TwoActions.png\" style=\"height:15px; padding:0px 2px 0px 2px\"/><img alt=\"Two Actions\" class=\"actionlight\" src=\"Images\\Actions\\TwoActions_I.png\" style=\"height:15px; padding:0px 2px 0px 2px\"/> (<a aonid=\"16\" game-obj=\"Traits\">auditory</a>, <a aonid=\"60\" game-obj=\"Traits\">emotion</a>, <a aonid=\"68\" game-obj=\"Traits\">fear</a>, <a aonid=\"106\" game-obj=\"Traits\">mental</a>) The skeleton removes its skull and throws it, making a jaws attack with a range of 20 feet. It then attempts to Demoralize each foe within 10 feet of the target. The head bounces, rolls, or even flies back, returning to the skeleton at the start of its next turn. The skeleton is blind until then.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 298
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "Made from bones held together by foul necromancy, skeletons are among the most common types of undead, found haunting old dungeons and forgotten cemeteries. ",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 298
            }
        }
